      "description": "The FEA modeling framework (multi-laboratory ensemble: FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading within pre-established acceptance criteria: less than 10% relative difference on all three QoIs and E/uval ratio below 1.96 across N=11 experimental constructs tested at two independent laboratories. This claim supports regulatory submission credibility for the Class II device.",
