    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted based on the regulatory precedent of ASTM F1717 as the standard test protocol for spinal implant constructs and the conservative nature of the single-condition test. All three primary QoIs pass pre-specified acceptance criteria with E/uval ratios well below 1.96. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU at Medium assurance level.",
